    3. Fault Confirmation

    Effective on: 001-100, 783-800, 850-874, 876, 894

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-710-050 -A0 - (20151101)

    A. Test
    (1) Do only the test of the pedestal and main panel integral lighting SEE AMM 33-13-00-710-001 .


    Effective on:  001-100, 783-800, 850-874, 876, 894
    Instrument and Panel Integral Lighting

    •

    If, during this operational test, on the the FLOOD LT/INTEG LT panel 111VU:

    When you turn the INTEG LT/MAIN PNL & PED potentiometer (17LF) from OFF to BRT SEE ASM 33-13-01 :

    (a) The integral lighting of one identification-plate does not operate, go to Para. 4.A.
    (b) The integral lighting of one instrument does not operate, go to Para. 4.B.
    (c) The integral lighting of more than one instrument and/or plate connected to the same fuse output does not operate, go to Para. 4.C.
    (d) The integral lighting of all the panels and/or the instruments does not operate, go to Para. 4.D.

    Effective on: 875, 877-893, 895-910, 928-950, 986-999

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-710-050 -B0 - (20170501)

    A. Test
    (1) Do only the test of the pedestal and main panel integral lighting SEE AMM 33-13-00-710-001 .
    •

    If, during this operational test, on the FLOOD LT/INTEG LT panel 111VU:

    When you turn the INT LT/MAIN PNL & PED potentiometer (17LF) from OFF to BRT SEE ASM 33-13-01 :

    (a) The integral lighting of one identification-plate does not operate, go to Para. 4.A.
    (b) The integral lighting of one instrument does not operate, go to Para. 4.B.
    (c) The integral lighting of more than one instrument connected to the same fuse output does not operate, go to Para. 4.C.
    (d) The integral lighting of all the panels and/or the instruments does not operate, go to Para. 4.D.
    (e) The integral lighting of more than one plate connected to the same pulse width modulation output does not operate, go to Para. 4.E.

    4. Fault Isolation

    Effective on: 001-100, 783-800, 850-874, 876, 894

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-810-050 -A0 - (20151101)

    A. The integral lighting of one identification-plate does not operate.
    (1) Remove the related integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AMM 33-13-41-000-001 or SEE AMM 33-13-43-000-801 .
    (2) Do a check for voltage at pin A/1 of the electrical connector of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate, SEE ASM 33-13-01 .
    (a) If there is no voltage:
    •

    Repair the wiring  between pin A/1 of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate and the first terminal block.

    (b) If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/N of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate, SEE ASM 33-13-01 :

    1 If there is a ground signal:
    a Replace the defective lamp of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate.
    NOTE:   
    Refer to the applicable CMM related to the P/N of the integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AIPC 33-13-08 for removal/installation instructions.
    2 If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring.

    •

    Install the related integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AMM 33-13-41-400-001 or SEE AMM 33-13-43-400-801 .


    Effective on: 875, 877-893, 895-910, 928-950, 986-999

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-810-050 -B0 - (20170501)

    A. The integral lighting of one plate does not operate.
    (1) Remove the related integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AMM 33-13-41-000-001 or SEE AMM 33-13-43-000-801 .
    (2) Do a check for continuity between the pin A/1 of the electrical connector of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate and the first terminal block SEE ASM 33-13-01 .
    (a) If there is no continuity:
    •

    Repair the wiring  between pin A/1 of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate and the first terminal block.

    (b) If there is continuity:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/N of the related integrally-lighted identification-plate, SEE ASM 33-13-01 :

    1 If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace the related integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AMM 33-13-41-400-001 or SEE AMM 33-13-43-400-801 .

    2 If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring.

    •

    Install the related integrally-lighted identification-plate SEE AMM 33-13-41-400-001 or SEE AMM 33-13-43-400-801 .


    Effective on: 001-999

    SUBTASK 33-13-00-810-058 -A0 - (20160501)

    B. The integral lighting of one instrument does not operate.
    (1) FOR 3CA3
    (a) Remove MCDU3 (3CA3) SEE AMM 22-82-12-000-001 .
    (b) Do a check for voltage at pin A/37 of the electrical connector of MCDU3 (3CA3) SEE ASM 33-13-01 .
    1 If there is no voltage:
    •

    2 If there is voltage:
    •

    Do a check for a ground signal at pin A/38 of the electrical connector of MCDU3 (3CA3), SEE ASM 33-13-01 .

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    Replace (3CA3)   SEE AMM 22-82-12-400-002 .

    b If there is no ground signal:
    •

    Repair the wiring from the MCDU3 (3CA3) pin A/37 to the ground terminal.

    •

    a If there is a ground signal:
    •

    b If there is no ground signal:

    •
